		<content translate="true">What Is Praise?</content>
	</text>
	<text id="nav_text" x="223" y="425" width="548" height="" autosize="H" style="PROMPT" visible="false" fx="PROMPT_SHOW" hidefx="PROMPT_HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Click a &lt;B&gt;Lesson&lt;/B&gt; or &lt;B&gt;Activity&lt;/B&gt; to learn more about &lt;B&gt;What Is Praise?&lt;/B&gt;</content>
	</text>
	<section id="presentation_text" align="LEFT" spacing="0x8" autospace="true" columns="0" exclusive="false" expanded="true">
		<text id="text01" x="370" y="60" width="386" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">According to research, the most effective praise is focused on efforts rather than outcomes.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text02" x="385" y="110" width="377" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Praise in this context is not conditional affection, but rather affirmation to the children of their genuine strengths.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text03" x="385" y="155" width="375" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Help children understand that a parents' love and overall acceptance of their child is not dependent on the child's accomplishments or behavior.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text04" x="385" y="275" width="380" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Both children and adults will repeat behaviors that feel good but will not repeat those that are unrewarding.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text05" x="385" y="275" width="391" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;B&gt;Key Message&lt;/B&gt;: &lt;LI&gt;Praise is a way of guiding children toward positive, appropriate behavior.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
	</section>
